        <abstract>
            <p>JS has now taken post of Curator of the Royal Botanic Garden, Calcutta.</p>
            <p>Wishes to vindicate himself of the charge that he pursued his experiments at Edinburgh to the detriment of his work.</p> 
<p>Apologises for poor quality of his <hi rend="italic">Verbascum</hi> paper, which was written from his notes during the passage to India [<hi rend="italic">J. Asiat. Soc. Bengal</hi> 36 (1865) pt 2: 145–74].</p> 
        </abstract>
